  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different jurisdictions:\n\n1. United States\n- Comprehensive Bank Secrecy Act and Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Strict reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Aggressive criminal prosecution\n- Emphasis on international cooperation\n\n2. European Union\n- Unified legal framework through Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Standardized reporting and due diligence requirements\n- Enhanced regulatory harmonization\n- Strong focus on transparency and information sharing\n\n3. United Kingdom\n- Sophisticated regulatory regime\n- Rigorous Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Substantial financial penalties for non-compliance\n- Specialized financial crime units\n\n4. Switzerland\n- Historically known for banking secrecy\n- Gradually increasing transparency\n- Strong international cooperation\n- Sophisticated compliance mechanisms\n\n5. China\n- Centralized regulatory approach\n- Strict government oversight\n- Increasing international alignment\n- Emphasis on preventing cross-border financial crimes\n\n6. Singapore\n- Stringent regulatory framework\n- Advanced technological monitoring\n- Strong international reputation\n- Proactive approach to financial crime prevention\n\n7. Russia\n- Less comprehensive regulatory environment\n- Evolving legal frameworks\n- Inconsistent enforcement\n- More limited international cooperation\n\nThese jurisdictions demonstrate varied but increasingly convergent approaches to combating money laundering.",
